1
00:00:02,498 --> 00:00:04,007
"Episode 3"

2
00:00:08,989 --> 00:00:11,418
I asked you for this earlier...

3
00:00:29,834 --> 00:00:31,378
-Good afternoon.
-Good afternoon.

4
00:00:33,189 --> 00:00:34,240
Kim Hyejin!

5
00:00:35,829 --> 00:00:36,967
What's going on with you?

6
00:00:37,067 --> 00:00:38,157
What are you doing here?

7
00:00:40,292 --> 00:00:41,772
It's great to see you, Sungjoon!

8
00:00:43,619 --> 00:00:44,541
Wait.

9
00:00:47,455 --> 00:00:49,139
I can't believe we're meeting here again!

10
00:00:49,239 --> 00:00:50,402
What brings you here?

11
00:00:52,829 --> 00:00:54,272
I want to ask you the same thing.

12
00:00:54,949 --> 00:00:56,832
I thought you were supposed
to be studying overseas.

13
00:00:56,932 --> 00:00:58,225
It's Manager Min's badge.

14
00:00:59,949 --> 00:01:00,960
Ms Min!

15
00:01:02,549 --> 00:01:04,336
Let's go talk someplace else.

16
00:01:04,831 --> 00:01:06,600
-Ms Min!
-Let's talk outside.

17
00:01:07,389 --> 00:01:08,289
Wait.

18
00:01:09,349 --> 00:01:11,333
Sir, you'll have to move your car.

19
00:01:11,433 --> 00:01:12,555
We're backed up.

20
00:01:13,149 --> 00:01:15,188
I understand, I'm sorry.
I'll move it right away.

21
00:01:17,869 --> 00:01:18,950
Wait here for me.

22
00:01:19,749 --> 00:01:20,697
Okay.

23
00:01:21,534 --> 00:01:23,185
Didn't you hear me calling for you?

24
00:01:23,405 --> 00:01:24,565
You've dropped this.

25
00:01:24,998 --> 00:01:26,713
What am I going to do?

26
00:01:27,476 --> 00:01:28,898
I'm going to lose my mind!

27
00:01:37,909 --> 00:01:40,946
As you already know...

28
00:01:41,885 --> 00:01:43,894
...I'm studying overseas.

29
00:01:44,189 --> 00:01:45,176
Yes, that's right.

30
00:01:45,589 --> 00:01:47,489
You even sent me a picture from London.

31
00:01:47,749 --> 00:01:52,151
Can you guess why I'm here now?

32
00:01:57,808 --> 00:01:58,828
Well...

33
00:01:59,709 --> 00:02:01,062
...I was over there.

34
00:02:01,770 --> 00:02:02,719
But...

35
00:02:05,869 --> 00:02:08,079
And shortly afterward,
I received a call from Korea.

36
00:02:08,652 --> 00:02:10,609
I was given an opportunity
to work in this hotel...

37
00:02:10,870 --> 00:02:12,222
...and I really wanted the job.

38
00:02:12,589 --> 00:02:15,829
And so, I was able to return
to Korea shortly afterward.

39
00:02:15,909 --> 00:02:16,855
Gosh.

40
00:02:16,955 --> 00:02:19,744
I'm not even famous,
but I've experienced so much!

41
00:02:36,349 --> 00:02:38,595
Then you should've told me
that you've returned.

42
00:02:40,269 --> 00:02:42,130
I almost left without saying hello to you

43
00:02:42,230 --> 00:02:43,872
because I thought you were in London.

44
00:02:44,469 --> 00:02:45,970
I thought I was seeing things.

45
00:02:48,589 --> 00:02:49,439
Do you see this?

46
00:02:49,539 --> 00:02:51,061
I'm getting goose bumps.

47
00:02:52,029 --> 00:02:54,629
You see, I was going
to contact you later today.

48
00:02:54,709 --> 00:02:57,460
But we happened to meet right here!

49
00:02:57,869 --> 00:02:58,948
Anyway, I think it's great.

50
00:02:59,389 --> 00:03:01,221
I was disappointed that you had
to leave like that.

51
00:03:01,869 --> 00:03:03,149
But I didn't expect this at all.

52
00:03:03,229 --> 00:03:05,909
I didn't imagine that
you'd become a hotelier.

53
00:03:06,269 --> 00:03:09,554
I couldn't imagine you'd be a deputy
chief editor for a fashion magazine.

54
00:03:11,829 --> 00:03:13,727
How did you know that
I'm a deputy chief editor?

55
00:03:14,629 --> 00:03:15,560
What?

56
00:03:16,589 --> 00:03:17,715
Well...

57
00:03:18,989 --> 00:03:21,766
...you told me when we met last time!

58
00:03:24,669 --> 00:03:25,924
Did I bring that up?

59
00:03:26,024 --> 00:03:27,092
Sure you did.

60
00:03:31,389 --> 00:03:33,170
Well, it's good to see you again.

61
00:03:34,073 --> 00:03:35,083
I know, right?

62
00:03:35,183 --> 00:03:38,032
Do you know the Jinsung Magazine
building past the intersection?

63
00:03:38,132 --> 00:03:39,533
That's where I work.

64
00:03:39,633 --> 00:03:41,703
It's pretty close, so we'll be able
to see each other often.

65
00:03:51,947 --> 00:03:54,429
"My Husband"

66
00:03:54,509 --> 00:03:56,325
Whose phone is that? Please answer it!

67
00:04:02,829 --> 00:04:04,306
-Yes, you've reached Kim...
-Hey!

68
00:04:04,896 --> 00:04:06,155
Oh, no! This is bad!

69
00:04:06,255 --> 00:04:07,697
Do you know who I met just now?

70
00:04:07,797 --> 00:04:08,827
My goodness.

71
00:04:09,429 --> 00:04:11,469
When you hear this,
you're going to freak out...

72
00:04:11,549 --> 00:04:12,709
The person whom...

73
00:04:13,069 --> 00:04:15,989
...you're trying to freak out
is not here at the moment.

74
00:04:18,195 --> 00:04:19,677
-Who is this?
-Kim Shinhyuk.

75
00:04:20,389 --> 00:04:22,460
-What?
-If it's something exciting...

76
00:04:22,560 --> 00:04:26,170
...you can tell me, and I'll
make sure she gets the message.

77
00:04:26,549 --> 00:04:27,713
What's he saying?

78
00:04:29,109 --> 00:04:30,214
No, it's okay.

79
00:04:30,314 --> 00:04:32,069
I'll call back later.

80
00:04:34,089 --> 00:04:35,108
Who was that?

81
00:04:35,926 --> 00:04:37,949
Did she really tender
her resignation or not?

82
00:04:39,949 --> 00:04:42,792
But I need to handle this right away!

83
00:04:49,789 --> 00:04:51,555
Hey, why are you coming home now?

84
00:04:51,949 --> 00:04:53,665
And why didn't you get your phone?

85
00:04:53,765 --> 00:04:55,723
Didn't some guy tell you
that I called earlier?

86
00:04:55,823 --> 00:04:57,534
No, that's not what's
important right now.

87
00:04:57,634 --> 00:04:59,507
Do you know what
happened at the hotel earlier?

88
00:04:59,607 --> 00:05:02,007
I've got the worst luck!
Don't be shocked, all right?

89
00:05:02,107 --> 00:05:03,684
At the hotel, I ran into...

90
00:05:03,784 --> 00:05:05,887
-Jerk!
-I met the jerk!

91
00:05:06,709 --> 00:05:07,629
What?

92
00:05:08,165 --> 00:05:10,062
I will not resign from this company!

93
00:05:11,669 --> 00:05:12,650
What's she saying?

94
00:05:13,149 --> 00:05:14,708
Jerk? Who?

95
00:05:15,874 --> 00:05:18,113
You didn't hand in your resignation?
I thought you were quitting today!

96
00:05:18,213 --> 00:05:19,469
Why should I? Why should I quit?

97
00:05:19,549 --> 00:05:21,409
I'm going to work at that company
with my head held high!

98
00:05:22,349 --> 00:05:23,975
So, you're no longer going to quit?

99
00:05:24,509 --> 00:05:27,181
Anyway, I completely support
your decision to stay.

100
00:05:27,281 --> 00:05:29,850
But why all of a sudden?
And who's this jerk you speak of?

101
00:05:29,950 --> 00:05:31,449
That jerk, Ji Sungjoon!

102
00:05:32,749 --> 00:05:34,492
So, the jerk is Ji Sungjoon?

103
00:05:34,592 --> 00:05:37,251
That's whom you're referring to?

104
00:05:38,549 --> 00:05:42,079
This morning, you were talking about
how you two have something special.

105
00:05:42,179 --> 00:05:43,572
Why are you calling him a jerk now?

106
00:05:44,326 --> 00:05:45,941
Do you know what he said to me?

107
00:05:46,041 --> 00:05:47,474
Let me tell you what he said to me!

108
00:05:53,069 --> 00:05:55,631
And that's what he said to me, that dog!

109
00:05:56,109 --> 00:05:57,431
No way...

110
00:05:57,749 --> 00:05:59,848
He seemed gentle and compassionate.

111
00:06:00,189 --> 00:06:01,549
And there's the verdict. He's a psycho.

112
00:06:01,629 --> 00:06:02,869
He's got multiple personalities.

113
00:06:02,949 --> 00:06:05,214
First love, my foot!
Feed him to the dogs!

114
00:06:07,309 --> 00:06:09,260
Wait, what's going on here?

115
00:06:10,309 --> 00:06:14,190
Now, that I think about it, lying about
studying abroad was the right decision.

116
00:06:14,290 --> 00:06:17,475
He's never going to find out...

117
00:06:17,789 --> 00:06:19,855
...so I would've cheated
myself by resigning!

118
00:06:20,269 --> 00:06:21,509
So, about that...

119
00:06:21,589 --> 00:06:25,146
He's got a rotten temper
and I can't stand the way he talks!

120
00:06:25,246 --> 00:06:27,961
Everyone in the office
calls him Crazy Joon!

121
00:06:29,029 --> 00:06:29,970
That's cold!

122
00:06:30,269 --> 00:06:33,154
He's always had an ulterior motive.

123
00:06:33,829 --> 00:06:35,215
He was returning to Korea...

124
00:06:35,315 --> 00:06:36,601
-...but he doesn't have a girlfriend.
-But he doesn't have a girlfriend.

125
00:06:36,701 --> 00:06:39,087
So, why not try and hit on
the prettiest girl at your old school?

126
00:06:39,709 --> 00:06:40,829
That's what he's up to!

127
00:06:41,549 --> 00:06:43,167
I've heard that someplace before.

128
00:06:43,267 --> 00:06:44,624
We're complete strangers now!

129
00:06:44,724 --> 00:06:47,206
I'm not going to worry about him
and only focus on work.

130
00:06:47,306 --> 00:06:49,710
So, don't you ever
bring him up in front of me again!

131
00:06:49,810 --> 00:06:50,832
Gosh, I hate him!

132
00:06:54,709 --> 00:06:55,657
Gosh.

133
00:06:55,757 --> 00:06:57,909
How did the situation turn like this?

134
00:06:58,509 --> 00:07:01,461
So, do I tell her that I met
Ji Sungjoon earlier today, or not?

135
00:07:01,561 --> 00:07:02,847
Oh, right.

136
00:07:02,947 --> 00:07:05,073
You mentioned that something
happened at the hotel.

137
00:07:05,629 --> 00:07:07,159
-What?
-What was it?

138
00:07:07,259 --> 00:07:09,041
You said that it was something urgent.

139
00:07:10,469 --> 00:07:11,418
I did?

140
00:07:12,789 --> 00:07:15,826
Oh, my. Why did I suddenly forget
what I was going to say?

141
00:07:16,429 --> 00:07:17,953
You've been drinking too much these days.

142
00:07:18,053 --> 00:07:21,339
Come on. Given our mood,
let's have one more beer tonight.

143
00:07:21,989 --> 00:07:22,974
Okay.

144
00:07:26,229 --> 00:07:29,187
Yes, she's determined
to keep her job now.

145
00:07:30,189 --> 00:07:31,897
Why tell her about it and make her worry?

146
00:07:33,469 --> 00:07:35,356
I'll just take care of it on my end.

147
00:08:16,349 --> 00:08:18,743
Americano Ristretto with triple shot.

148
00:08:23,629 --> 00:08:26,233
Here is your Americano Ristretto
with triple shot.

149
00:08:29,549 --> 00:08:30,507
Sir?

150
00:08:32,069 --> 00:08:32,987
Sir.

151
00:08:33,989 --> 00:08:35,560
-Yes.
-Here's your coffee.

152
00:08:36,029 --> 00:08:37,215
Oh, thank you very much.

153
00:08:47,309 --> 00:08:49,298
Oh, my. What's the matter with him?

154
00:09:13,629 --> 00:09:14,973
It's go time!

155
00:09:23,269 --> 00:09:24,806
It's go time!

156
00:09:25,309 --> 00:09:28,309
Why do you always say that
when it's time to cross?

157
00:09:28,389 --> 00:09:29,949
Because a green light tells you
to go ahead and cross.

158
00:09:30,029 --> 00:09:31,167
What about the red lights?

159
00:09:31,267 --> 00:09:32,401
The red lights?

160
00:09:32,501 --> 00:09:34,313
The red lights are red lights.

161
00:09:34,909 --> 00:09:36,374
But that's a little weird.

162
00:09:36,869 --> 00:09:38,507
My whole family says that.

163
00:09:38,869 --> 00:09:40,980
But now that you mention it,
it is a bit weird.

164
00:09:46,669 --> 00:09:48,551
Yes, just focus on your salary.

165
00:09:49,029 --> 00:09:50,915
-Salary, salary.
-Jackson!

166
00:09:51,829 --> 00:09:52,869
Good morning!

167
00:09:52,949 --> 00:09:53,957
Do you want a bite?

168
00:09:54,509 --> 00:09:55,975
-No.
-Why not?

169
00:09:56,561 --> 00:10:01,149
I've had just one bite. Try it!

170
00:10:12,797 --> 00:10:14,293
"Sungjoon"
Oh, no.

171
00:10:14,393 --> 00:10:15,597
It's Ji Sungjoon!

172
00:10:19,869 --> 00:10:20,996
Yes, Sungjoon.

173
00:10:21,349 --> 00:10:23,012
Yes, Hyejin. Where are you right now?

174
00:10:23,569 --> 00:10:24,743
I'm at home.

175
00:10:25,749 --> 00:10:26,953
But why do you ask?

176
00:10:27,309 --> 00:10:29,398
I was wondering if you
were headed to work.

177
00:10:29,749 --> 00:10:30,834
No.

178
00:10:32,229 --> 00:10:34,414
But why are you asking me that
all of a sudden?

179
00:10:35,309 --> 00:10:37,649
I was at the crosswalk,
and it reminded me of you...

180
00:10:39,229 --> 00:10:40,215
Never mind.

181
00:10:40,709 --> 00:10:42,992
Go on and get ready for work.
We'll talk again later.

182
00:10:43,092 --> 00:10:44,215
I'll call back soon.

183
00:10:44,509 --> 00:10:45,546
Hey, Sungjoon.

184
00:10:47,109 --> 00:10:48,094
Yes?

185
00:10:48,669 --> 00:10:50,177
When do you have some time?

186
00:10:50,709 --> 00:10:52,149
I have something to tell you.

187
00:10:54,229 --> 00:10:55,328
Let's meet up.

188
00:10:57,109 --> 00:11:00,734
Sir, why don't you take a coffee break?

189
00:11:00,834 --> 00:11:02,461
No coffee. I'm taking herbal medication.

190
00:11:03,204 --> 00:11:05,607
But this coffee is filled
with my affection.

191
00:11:06,429 --> 00:11:07,524
Go for it!

192
00:11:09,789 --> 00:11:10,709
I said I don't want any!

193
00:11:10,789 --> 00:11:13,212
Joonwoo, your morning coffee.

194
00:11:14,829 --> 00:11:16,420
-You're tired, aren't you?
-Thank you.

195
00:11:18,469 --> 00:11:20,669
-How are you today?
-Mr Kim, good morning!

196
00:11:20,749 --> 00:11:21,940
This is for you.

197
00:11:22,040 --> 00:11:23,070
I don't have any money.

198
00:11:23,170 --> 00:11:24,450
If you're trying get money,
look elsewhere.

199
00:11:25,355 --> 00:11:27,492
You're so funny, Mr Kim!

200
00:11:27,592 --> 00:11:28,976
Such a jokester!

201
00:11:30,589 --> 00:11:31,768
What's with her?

202
00:11:33,549 --> 00:11:34,699
Did she put something in here?

203
00:11:36,069 --> 00:11:37,770
Jackson, want to give this a try?

204
00:11:39,709 --> 00:11:41,672
Seol, I want coffee, too...

205
00:11:41,772 --> 00:11:43,092
I'm so sleepy.

206
00:11:43,192 --> 00:11:44,389
Then why don't you go for a jog?

207
00:11:44,469 --> 00:11:46,452
Fresh air is the best
when you're feeling sleepy.

208
00:11:49,509 --> 00:11:51,436
Oh, my goodness... What's with her?

209
00:11:51,869 --> 00:11:54,210
I'm her superior,
so why is she neglecting me?

210
00:11:56,069 --> 00:11:57,145
Good morning.

211
00:11:57,245 --> 00:11:58,758
-How are you?
-You've arrived?

212
00:12:02,356 --> 00:12:03,807
Crazy Joon has entered the building.

213
00:12:04,173 --> 00:12:06,949
He's prepared to devour us again today.

214
00:12:07,029 --> 00:12:09,791
Get ready for
his barrage of insults again.

215
00:12:10,309 --> 00:12:12,147
We have a meeting in 10 minutes.

216
00:12:17,325 --> 00:12:18,429
Three months will go by quickly.

217
00:12:18,509 --> 00:12:21,150
Whatever I do here,
time will keep ticking.

218
00:12:22,749 --> 00:12:24,029
I'm not going to cower
like an idiot anymore.

219
00:12:24,109 --> 00:12:25,638
I was the ace of the management team!

220
00:12:25,738 --> 00:12:28,590
I'll show them what I'm made of!

221
00:12:37,749 --> 00:12:41,531
Next issue, we're planning on
grooming and cosmeceutical brands.

222
00:12:41,631 --> 00:12:42,990
What? A cos-what?

223
00:12:43,090 --> 00:12:47,820
People are willing to spend
on fashion and cosmetics now.

224
00:12:48,106 --> 00:12:49,909
So, as far as grooming is concerned...

225
00:12:49,989 --> 00:12:51,069
Is this outer space?

226
00:12:51,149 --> 00:12:54,246
Why is everyone talking gibberish?
I don't understand any of this!

227
00:12:54,709 --> 00:12:56,184
We've already heard
this kind of theme before

228
00:12:56,284 --> 00:13:00,142
so I want you to provide more specifics.

229
00:13:00,863 --> 00:13:02,551
-Okay.
-Next, the fashion team?

230
00:13:04,029 --> 00:13:07,676
We're thinking about featuring
fashion in movies by the era.

231
00:13:07,776 --> 00:13:10,749
We can research
the Garconne look of the 1920s...

232
00:13:10,829 --> 00:13:11,784
A what-son?

233
00:13:12,189 --> 00:13:13,824
What kind of son is him?

234
00:13:13,924 --> 00:13:15,379
Or a 40s military look.

235
00:13:16,029 --> 00:13:18,071
We can correlate the era to each trend

236
00:13:18,171 --> 00:13:23,674
by providing parallels
to specific movie frames.

237
00:13:24,309 --> 00:13:27,452
I've prepared some still shots of some
of the movies we've reviewed.

238
00:13:27,869 --> 00:13:28,802
Hyejin.

239
00:13:29,909 --> 00:13:31,194
Hyejin, can you turn on the monitor?

240
00:13:31,709 --> 00:13:33,021
What's a monitor?

241
00:13:34,429 --> 00:13:36,886
Oh, monitor.

242
00:13:37,669 --> 00:13:38,510
Okay.

243
00:13:51,020 --> 00:13:53,193
Why isn't this turning on?

244
00:13:55,245 --> 00:13:58,080
Well, Hyejin. That's not the one.

245
00:14:03,229 --> 00:14:04,473
I'm so sorry.

246
00:14:11,909 --> 00:14:12,886
Gosh!

247
00:14:18,140 --> 00:14:20,300
Hyejin, the remote for the stand...

248
00:14:21,794 --> 00:14:22,883
I'm so sorry!

249
00:14:22,983 --> 00:14:26,863
I thought I already told you
that I don't like to waste time!

250
00:14:32,829 --> 00:14:36,149
Develop your ideas from today,
and be prepared to present them.

251
00:14:37,469 --> 00:14:40,463
Oh, and who's taking the minutes?

252
00:14:42,418 --> 00:14:43,564
That would be me.

253
00:14:49,029 --> 00:14:50,429
Bring it to me as soon as it's prepared.

254
00:14:50,509 --> 00:14:51,381
Yes, sir.

255
00:14:51,909 --> 00:14:54,404
-Good work everyone.
-Good work everyone.

256
00:14:54,939 --> 00:14:57,202
Hyejin, you were hilarious today.

257
00:15:03,235 --> 00:15:04,784
Why did you have to do that?

258
00:15:07,229 --> 00:15:08,953
-Look here, Support.
-Yes, Mr Ji!

259
00:15:11,509 --> 00:15:13,924
