You're nothing but a bum!

788
00:49:47,695 --> 00:49:49,589
-Hey, come here!
-Sir.

789
00:49:49,669 --> 00:49:50,709
Come here!

790
00:49:50,989 --> 00:49:52,919
-Let go.
-Let go!

791
00:49:53,019 --> 00:49:54,750
You come here!

792
00:49:55,189 --> 00:49:56,389
-Come here!
-Sir!

793
00:49:56,469 --> 00:49:58,292
Let go! Let go!

794
00:49:59,737 --> 00:50:01,068
That stings.

795
00:50:01,669 --> 00:50:03,477
What kind of psychopath was that?

796
00:50:10,109 --> 00:50:12,686
-Who are you?
-You don't have to know who I am.

797
00:50:13,549 --> 00:50:15,090
Go and apologize to the woman.

798
00:50:16,309 --> 00:50:17,326
I'll give you three minutes.

799
00:50:19,869 --> 00:50:21,439
What gives you the right
to give me three minutes?

800
00:50:21,539 --> 00:50:22,730
Do I look like a microwave to you?

801
00:50:23,069 --> 00:50:25,798
I should be filing charges,
not apologizing to her.

802
00:50:28,149 --> 00:50:31,148
That Crazy Joon! Why is he so difficult?

803
00:50:31,469 --> 00:50:34,589
Did he shoot down
all of our ideas at the meeting?

804
00:50:34,669 --> 00:50:38,344
No, I think a few made it through.

805
00:50:38,444 --> 00:50:39,944
-How do you know that?
-What are you saying?

806
00:50:40,044 --> 00:50:41,669
I can read him now.

807
00:50:41,749 --> 00:50:44,189
Watch his arms during the meetings.

808
00:50:44,269 --> 00:50:46,158
-His arms?
-What about his arms?

809
00:50:47,269 --> 00:50:51,109
You're running out of time,
so go and apologize.

810
00:50:54,309 --> 00:50:55,918
Do you hear that barking, too?

811
00:51:04,989 --> 00:51:07,357
I despise wasting time for no reason.

812
00:51:08,669 --> 00:51:13,409
When he decides on something,
he rolls up his sleeves.

813
00:51:13,989 --> 00:51:15,296
I think it's his habit.

814
00:51:23,445 --> 00:51:25,229
Mister, please let me off here.

815
00:51:26,749 --> 00:51:27,709
Are you okay?

816
00:51:30,272 --> 00:51:31,167
Yes.

817
00:51:31,669 --> 00:51:32,611
Let's go.

818
00:51:34,427 --> 00:51:35,738
What's the matter?

819
00:51:39,709 --> 00:51:41,217
Gosh...

820
00:51:42,322 --> 00:51:43,447
Let's leave for now.

821
00:52:07,469 --> 00:52:08,775
What's that face?

822
00:52:09,920 --> 00:52:13,182
Excuse me, I'm looking for
a woman who came here alone.

823
00:52:13,282 --> 00:52:15,549
Oh, you're the wife from earlier!

824
00:52:15,629 --> 00:52:16,509
What?

825
00:52:16,589 --> 00:52:18,465
Yes, that's right. I'm the wife.

826
00:52:18,565 --> 00:52:19,806
Where's my friend?

827
00:52:19,906 --> 00:52:21,243
Didn't you see her on your way in here?

828
00:52:21,343 --> 00:52:24,869
Some guy came by and took her away.

829
00:52:25,429 --> 00:52:26,464
A guy?

830
00:52:28,589 --> 00:52:29,614
Who could it be?

831
00:52:30,589 --> 00:52:32,640
Was it the man she was kissing
in front of the house?

832
00:52:39,971 --> 00:52:41,982
Write your name
and date of birth right here.

833
00:52:47,149 --> 00:52:49,070
Did you change your name recently?

834
00:52:50,326 --> 00:52:51,537
You've spelled your name wrong.

835
00:52:53,279 --> 00:52:54,172
Right.

836
00:52:54,509 --> 00:52:56,556
I think I got so angry
that I've lost my mind.

837
00:52:56,656 --> 00:52:57,548
Hand it over.

838
00:53:01,869 --> 00:53:03,629
Mister, don't you need
to be treated as well?

839
00:53:04,149 --> 00:53:05,069
What?

840
00:53:05,149 --> 00:53:07,687
I think he's cut himself on the face.

841
00:53:09,629 --> 00:53:10,697
Your face.

842
00:53:15,549 --> 00:53:16,954
It's okay. It's nothing.

843
00:53:17,054 --> 00:53:19,488
No it's not, it might scar!

844
00:53:21,269 --> 00:53:23,020
I'm really fine, Miss Kim Hyejin.

845
00:53:32,109 --> 00:53:35,425
You've had a tetanus shot,
but don't forget to take your medication.

846
00:53:35,989 --> 00:53:36,997
I'm going to check.

847
00:53:37,589 --> 00:53:38,490
Okay.

848
00:53:41,309 --> 00:53:43,198
But why don't you ask me anything?

849
00:53:44,109 --> 00:53:45,010
About what?

850
00:53:45,110 --> 00:53:49,953
I stood you up
and I was found drinking by myself.

851
00:53:52,669 --> 00:53:54,246
I'm sure something bothered you.

852
00:53:55,149 --> 00:53:56,615
I'm sure it's not fun to talk about...

853
00:53:56,949 --> 00:53:58,612
...so I didn't want to bring it up.

854
00:54:03,549 --> 00:54:05,296
I wanted to see you today because...

855
00:54:05,396 --> 00:54:06,298
Follow me.

856
00:54:06,749 --> 00:54:07,778
Where are we going?

857
00:54:08,909 --> 00:54:09,972
Thank you.

858
00:54:15,509 --> 00:54:17,979
That's probably full of calories.

859
00:54:18,079 --> 00:54:20,240
You need to eat
if you want to take your medication.

860
00:54:21,761 --> 00:54:24,224
And it'll help with your hangover
because you've had a lot to drink.

861
00:54:24,989 --> 00:54:28,184
Then maybe I'll have a bite?

862
00:54:44,389 --> 00:54:45,840
This doesn't taste like it, either.

863
00:54:48,216 --> 00:54:52,942
Remember I used to be fat?

864
00:54:53,042 --> 00:54:55,736
Hey, you weren't just fat.
You were like a pig...

865
00:54:56,669 --> 00:55:00,426
I mean, you were cuddly.

866
00:55:04,349 --> 00:55:08,800
Well, my mom used to feed me this
because she thought I looked gaunt.

867
00:55:09,389 --> 00:55:11,889
I hated to eat it back then...

868
00:55:12,949 --> 00:55:15,868
...but I started missing it
after she died.

869
00:55:17,074 --> 00:55:19,664
No matter where I go,
I can't find the same taste.

870
00:55:23,619 --> 00:55:24,816
I missed how it tasted.

871
00:55:25,589 --> 00:55:27,031
She cooked it for hours...

872
00:55:28,962 --> 00:55:30,722
...in front of the fire.

873
00:55:31,909 --> 00:55:34,561
But she can't do that for me anymore.

874
00:55:38,149 --> 00:55:39,785
I guess that's why I missed it.

875
00:55:44,229 --> 00:55:46,795
I think I'm able to say these things
because it's you.

876
00:55:50,909 --> 00:55:55,619
It's been a while since I met someone
whom I can be myself with.

877
00:56:01,509 --> 00:56:02,433
Let's eat.

878
00:56:02,869 --> 00:56:03,767
Okay.

879
00:56:06,149 --> 00:56:07,007
Oh, right!

880
00:56:07,107 --> 00:56:08,349
Why did you want to meet me earlier today?

881
00:56:08,429 --> 00:56:09,545
You wanted to tell me something?

882
00:56:21,589 --> 00:56:22,615
What's this?

883
00:56:25,109 --> 00:56:26,494
It seems to be Ms Min's handwriting.

884
00:56:27,882 --> 00:56:29,971
I saw her writing that earlier today.

885
00:56:30,776 --> 00:56:32,378
"I'm reassigned to Jeju Island."

886
00:56:32,709 --> 00:56:35,170
"The man I'm supposed
to marry hates me meeting other men."

887
00:56:35,270 --> 00:56:36,901
"I get fired and go overseas again."

888
00:56:38,383 --> 00:56:40,208
"The entire family
moves out of the country."

889
00:56:40,308 --> 00:56:41,389
What's this all about?

890
00:56:41,469 --> 00:56:43,892
Which is the option
that she wants to happen?

891
00:56:45,789 --> 00:56:47,197
Hello, Miss Kim Hyejin.

892
00:56:48,269 --> 00:56:50,749
Why are you speechless all of a sudden?

893
00:56:51,909 --> 00:56:55,457
Is it hard to talk about?

894
00:56:57,189 --> 00:56:58,328
No.

895
00:56:59,509 --> 00:57:05,669
I felt bad for leaving you
hanging at the hotel...

896
00:57:06,114 --> 00:57:10,104
...so I wanted to buy you dinner.

897
00:57:11,709 --> 00:57:13,241
I thought it was about something else.

898
00:57:14,229 --> 00:57:16,436
You're rather bland sometimes.

899
00:57:17,109 --> 00:57:20,174
If I'm bland,
would you like some salt with it?

900
00:57:22,526 --> 00:57:23,931
Eat before it gets cold.

901
00:57:25,229 --> 00:57:26,181
Okay.

902
00:57:29,469 --> 00:57:32,961
Yes, you were injured because of me...

903
00:57:34,629 --> 00:57:36,281
...so maybe I shouldn't tell you today.

904
00:57:37,660 --> 00:57:39,319
I'll tell you later.

905
00:57:39,989 --> 00:57:43,172
I heard that the world is
only that which you can see.

906
00:57:44,069 --> 00:57:48,626
The same might go for human beings.

907
00:57:51,349 --> 00:57:53,029
Why isn't she coming?

908
00:57:53,109 --> 00:57:54,149
Hey, Hari.

909
00:57:56,589 --> 00:57:58,471
What was that text message about earlier?

910
00:57:58,571 --> 00:57:59,542
Are you okay?

911
00:58:00,269 --> 00:58:01,375
What's wrong with your hand?

912
00:58:01,475 --> 00:58:02,419
Were you injured?

913
00:58:02,519 --> 00:58:04,588
Hey, what happened? Is it bad?

914
00:58:04,688 --> 00:58:06,029
I fell and injured myself a little bit.

915
00:58:06,109 --> 00:58:07,829
This isn't a little bit.

916
00:58:07,909 --> 00:58:09,992
Girl, you should've been more careful!

917
00:58:10,092 --> 00:58:12,053
-I'm fine.
-Hey, let's go inside.

918
00:58:12,509 --> 00:58:14,162
Why did you have to hurt yourself?

919
00:58:14,262 --> 00:58:16,648
"Prescription: Kim Hyejin"

920
00:58:18,429 --> 00:58:20,768
When you don't care, you can't see.

921
00:58:25,429 --> 00:58:26,549
Did you make it home safely?

922
00:58:27,069 --> 00:58:29,215
Be careful until your hands
are completely healed.

923
00:58:29,749 --> 00:58:31,873
Good night and I'll see you soon.

924
00:58:33,269 --> 00:58:35,450
The more you discover,

925
00:58:35,550 --> 00:58:38,963
the more clearly
you begin to see the person.

926
00:58:40,029 --> 00:58:42,639
Like Hari on that day.

927
00:58:49,869 --> 00:58:53,017
Here's the Americano Ristretto
that you've ordered.

928
00:58:53,669 --> 00:58:54,629
Sir?

929
00:58:56,525 --> 00:58:57,457
Sir?

930
00:58:58,349 --> 00:58:59,429
Here's your coffee.

931
00:58:59,509 --> 00:59:00,546
Oh, thank you.

932
00:59:15,189 --> 00:59:16,471
Yes, this is Ji Sungjoon.

933
00:59:17,109 --> 00:59:18,483
You've sent me an email?

934
00:59:18,949 --> 00:59:21,123
I'll check it right away
and call you back.

935
00:59:28,869 --> 00:59:30,389
I don't have time to eat with you.

936
00:59:30,469 --> 00:59:32,262
Go straight home, okay baby?

937
00:59:32,909 --> 00:59:34,875
Hey, don't go and see Hari either!

938
00:59:34,975 --> 00:59:36,226
You never listen to me!

939
00:59:36,829 --> 00:59:38,536
Kim Hyerin, are you serious?

940
00:59:38,636 --> 00:59:40,563
All right, I'm going. I'll see you there.

941
00:59:41,469 --> 00:59:43,198
Who does she take after?

942
00:59:45,829 --> 00:59:47,221
That belongs to me.

943
00:59:56,325 --> 00:59:58,350
Gosh, I can't stand her!

944
01:00:22,777 --> 01:00:24,350
"She Was Pretty"

945
01:00:24,450 --> 01:00:27,935
What makes you any better than me?

946
01:00:28,035 --> 01:00:29,549
After neglecting me like this,

947
01:00:29,629 --> 01:00:33,069
imagine him finding out
that I'm his first love.

948
01:00:33,149 --> 01:00:34,189
He can never find out!

949
01:00:34,269 --> 01:00:36,313
I should tell him everything!

950
01:00:36,413 --> 01:00:38,354
You act like you know Mr Ji.

951
01:00:38,454 --> 01:00:39,782
To be honest...
